The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, visited R&J Johnson Farms in Glyndon, Minnesota to discuss the importance of agriculture and expanded trade. He emphasized the need for fair and reciprocal trade deals, mentioning ongoing negotiations with China and the recently approved trade deal with Mexico and Canada (USMCA). Pence called on Congressman Collin Peterson, Chairman of the House Agriculture Committee, to urge Speaker Nancy Pelosi to bring the USMCA to the floor for a vote. He also addressed concerns about the impact of the trade dispute with China on American farmers and mentioned the possibility of providing additional support if needed. Pence highlighted the benefits of the USMCA for American farmers and workers and expressed optimism that it would pass in Congress.